pl.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = (9,2)

def prepare_plot(title, y_label, x_label):
    pl.figure()
    pl.title(title)
    pl.ylabel(y_label)
    pl.xlabel(x_label)
    
def twin_plot(xy_data1, xy_data2, title='', xlabel='', ylabel1='', ylabel2=''):
    pl.title(title)
    pl.plot(*xy_data1, color='b')
    pl.ylabel(ylabel1, color='b')
    pl.xlabel(xlabel)

    ax2 = pl.gca().twinx()
    pl.plot(*xy_data2, color='g')
    pl.ylabel(ylabel2, color='g')

def zplane(zeros, poles):
    """
    Plot the complex z-plane given zeros and poles.
    """
    zeros=np.array(zeros);
    poles=np.array(poles);
    ax = pl.gca()

    # Add unit circle and zero axes    
    unit_circle = pl.matplotlib.patches.Circle((0,0), radius=1, fill=False,
                                 color='black', ls='solid', alpha=0.6)
    ax.add_patch(unit_circle)
    pl.axvline(0, color='0.7')
    pl.axhline(0, color='0.7')

    #Rescale to a nice size
    rscale = 1.2 * np.amax(np.concatenate((abs(zeros), abs(poles), [1])))
    pl.axis('scaled')
    pl.axis([-rscale, rscale, -rscale, rscale])
    
    # Plot the poles and zeros
    polesplot = pl.plot(poles.real, poles.imag, 'x', markersize=9)
    zerosplot = pl.plot(zeros.real, zeros.imag,  'o', markersize=9, color='none', 
                             markeredgecolor=polesplot[0].get_color(), 
                             )

    #Draw overlap text
    overlap_txt = []
    def draw_overlap_text():
        for txt in overlap_txt:
            try:    txt.remove()
            except: txt.set_visible(False)
        del overlap_txt[:]

        poles_pixel_positions = ax.transData.transform(np.vstack(polesplot[0].get_data()).T)
        zeros_pixel_positions = ax.transData.transform(np.vstack(zerosplot[0].get_data()).T)

        for (zps_pixels, zps) in [(poles_pixel_positions, poles), (zeros_pixel_positions, zeros)]:
            superscript = np.ones(len(zps))
            for i in range(len(zps)):
                for j in range(i+1,len(zps)):
                    if superscript[i]!=-1:
                        if np.all(np.abs(zps_pixels[i] - zps_pixels[j]) < 0.9):
                            superscript[i]+=1;
                            superscript[j]=-1;
            for i in range(len(zps)):
                if superscript[i] > 1:
                    txt = pl.text(zps[i].real, zps[i].imag,
                            r'${}^{%d}$'%superscript[i], fontsize=20
                            )
                    overlap_txt.append(txt)
    draw_overlap_text()

    #Reset when zooming
    def on_zoom_change(axes): draw_overlap_text()
    ax.callbacks.connect('xlim_changed', on_zoom_change)
    ax.callbacks.connect('ylim_changed', on_zoom_change)

def vary_variable(R1, THETA_1, R2, THETA_2):
    for r1 in R1:
        for theta1 in THETA_1:
            for r2 in R2:
                for theta2 in THETA_2:
                    z = [complex(r1*np.cos(theta1),r1*np.sin(theta1)), complex(r1*np.cos(-theta1),r1*np.sin(-theta1))]
                    p = [complex(r2*np.cos(theta2),r2*np.sin(theta2)), complex(r2*np.cos(-theta2),r2*np.sin(-theta2))]
                    b, a = signal.zpk2tf(z, p, 1)
                    d, c = signal.freqz(b, a)
                    magnitude = 20*np.log10(abs(c))
                    phase = np.unwrap(np.angle(c))
                    
                    #Question A
                    pl.figure(figsize=(12,4))
                    zplane(z, p)
                    pl.show()
                    
                    #Question B
                    pl.figure(figsize=(12,4))
                    twin_plot((d, magnitude),(d, phase), 'Magnitude & Phase Response', 'Frequency', 'Magnitude', 'Phase')
                    pl.show()
                    
                    #Question C
                    impulse = np.zeros(50)
                    impulse[2] = 1
                    filter_ = signal.lfilter(b, a, impulse)
                    pl.plot(filter_)
                    pl.show()

z = [complex(1*np.cos(theta1),1*np.sin(theta1)), complex(1*np.cos(-theta1),1*np.sin(-theta1))]
p = [complex(r2*np.cos(theta2),r2*np.sin(theta2)), complex(r2*np.cos(-theta2),r1*np.sin(-theta2))]
b, a = signal.zpk2tf(z, p, 1)
d, c = signal.freqz(b, a)

def wave(f):
    w = 2*np.pi*f
    tot = 10
    t = np.arange(0, tot/f, 1)
    x = np.sin(w*t)
    return x

pl.figure(figsize=(12,3))
for f in [0.11, 0.125, 0.135]:
    wave_ = wave(f)
    output = signal.lfilter(b, a, wave_)
    pl.plot(output)
